blueprint.description: Pre-spaceflight Turbine array for Nauvis. Meant to provide 1.1 GW on fuel cells alone. The Heating Tower version can be hard-stamped on top of it after visiting Gleba.
blueprint.label: Early 1.1 GW Nauvis Powerplant [planet=nauvis]

blueprint.description: 1.1 GW Hybrid Plant for Nauvis. Laterally tile-able. When Nuclear plants run low on temperature, heating towers are fueled.
blueprint.label: 1.1 GW Hybrid Power Plant [planet=nauvis]

blueprint.description:
Adapts the 1.1GW tile-able powerplant array for Gleba, but prioritizes rocket fuel over fuel cells once regualrly running. If no rocket fuel is available, the plant switches to nuclear power.

Also, with a large enough island, you can use this powerplant on Fulgora. Just don't forget to add lightning rods.
blueprint.label: 1.1 GW Gleban/Fulgoran Powerplant variant [planet=gleba][planet=fulgora]

blueprint.description:
This 1.1 Gigawatt array runs off of Calcite and Sulfuric Acid as its primary source of power. If either are low, the plant switches to rocket fuel and an alarm goes off.

It should be noted, however, that solar is much more reliable than rocket fuel; the latter should function as a tertiary power back up.

alert_parameters.alert_message: Sulfuric acid or calcite is low!

blueprint.label: 1.1 GW Vulcanus Hybrid Power Plant #1 [recipe=acid-neutralisation][planet=vulcanus]

blueprint.description: Variant of the 1.1 Gigawatt hybrid array that uses cryo plants instead of chemical plants.

alert_parameters.alert_message: Sulfuric acid or calcite is low!

blueprint.label: 1.1 GW Vulcanus Hybrid Powerplant #2 [recipe=acid-neutralisation][planet=vulcanus]

blueprint.description:
This compact, tile-able 58 megawatt powerplant makes use of three modes of power:
- To startup, the array captures lightning through two lightning rods and stores power in 10 accumulators.
- To speed up the process of boiling water to 500 C, a nuclear plant can be used, feeding on fuel cells.
- Main power is provided by 2 heating towers feeding off solid fuel.
blueprint.label: 58 MW Compact Hybrid Power Setup [planet=fulgora]

blueprint.description:
A tile-able, compact 34.9 MW Power array. For power startup on Aquilo:
- With an offshore pump, syphon the surrounding ammonia sea and feed it into a chemical plant that splits it into ice and ammonia. Make sure that it's heated. A nuclear plant is best.
- Pump oil from nearby patches and combine ammonia and oil into solid fuel. Make sure that the jacks are similarly heated.
- Feed solid fuel on one side of the fuel belt and fuel cells on the other. Manually insert fuel cells into the nuke plant
blueprint.label: 35 MW Hybrid Powerplant [planet=aquilo]
